n universalistic terms, while leveraging their standing as representatives of growing minority populations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aPressure groupszUnited States. 4aPolicy. 4aPolitics -- United States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / National.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804767750zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804767750423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804767750/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles